title: HKSAR Delegation returned to Hong Kong after attending the "Tenth Anniversary Commemoration of the Fourth World Conference on Women"
content_text:
p>A delegation from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) attended 
the "Tenth Anniversary Commemoration of the Fourth World Conference on Women" 
held on August 29 to September 1, 2005 at Beijing and returned today (September 
2). The Conference attracted participants from around the world to exchange on 
the theme "Towards Gender Equality and Common Development".  The 30-strong HKSAR delegation, led by the Permanent Secretary for Health, 
Welfare and Food, Mrs Carrie Yau, attended the Conference including six thematic

Welfare and Food, Mrs Carrie Yau, attended the Conference including six thematic 
workshops on "Women in Decision-making and Management", "Economic Empowerment of 
Women", "Women's Human Rights and the Elimination of Violence against Women", 
"Women and Sustainable Development", "Women and Poverty Eradication" and "Women 
and HIV/AIDS". Members of the delegation also joined the visit to Huairou, where 
the 1995 NGO Forum on Women was held. The "Beijing Plus 10 Declaration: Solidarity for Gender Equality, Development

and Peace" was unanimously endorsed at the Conference. Delegates from all over 
the world applauding the contributions of women in different aspects and 
reaffirmed their commitments to the Beijing Declaration and the Beijing Platform 
for Action. They also shared and exchanged experiences, achievements and 
barriers in advancing the interests and status of women in their countries or 
places over the past decade. They committed to continue to spare no efforts to 
speed up the full and effective implementation of the Beijing Platform for

speed up the full and effective implementation of the Beijing Platform for 
Action with a view to realising equality between women and men.  The HKSAR Government also took part in the "Exhibition on the Ten-Year Progress 
and Development of Chinese Women" held between August 30 and September 4, 2005 
at the Beijing Nationalities Cultural Palace to showcase the achievements made 
in Hong Kong with the joint efforts of all sectors.
